    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A bright red synthetic organic pigment made from the deposition of eosin on a alumina trihydrate base, typically used in illustrations and prints but not in paintings; the color fades in daylight.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種以合成法製成的有機亮紅色顏料，取自三水合氧化鋁基底上的曙紅沉積物，此種顏料經過日光照射後會褪色；通常於製作插圖及印刷時使用，但不做為繪畫顏料。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
